### English Title:
Tesla Reaches Settlement in Racial Discrimination Lawsuit Filed by Black Employee

### English Text Summary:
Tesla has reached a settlement in a racial discrimination lawsuit filed by a Black employee, Raina Pierce, who alleged that a manager at the Fremont, California factory made racist remarks. The settlement, proposed by a mediator, has not disclosed its terms. Pierce reported extensive harassment, including racist graffiti and gender-based insults, and claimed she faced disciplinary actions for behavior that was overlooked for non-Black employees. Tesla has faced other discrimination allegations at the Fremont factory, including a previous case where a plaintiff received a $3.2 million settlement after a jury verdict.

